<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - HIGH-PRESSURE OIL PUMP - Installation - High-pressure Oil Pump
        Cover
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26511.4.3" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="5">
        <title>High-pressure Oil Pump Cover</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a new gasket in the recess of cover for the high-pressure oil pump (if not already
                done).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651125" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D1399.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Lubricate O-ring in recess of cover for high-pressure oil pump</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate O-ring in recess of cover for high-pressure oil pump.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply liquid gasket at two locations where rear cover and the crankcase meet.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651127" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D1387.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installation of high-pressure oil pump cover</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not drop the three mounting bolts inside high-pressure oil pump cover
                    to be mounted under the EGR cooler.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install three bolts in the part of the cover that will go under the EGR cooler.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651128" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D13100.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Seating high-pressure oil pump cover</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply firm even downward pressure to seat the high-pressure oil pump cover on O-ring.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage and cracking the cover plate, the high-pressure oil pump cover must be
                    firmly seated on the O-ring.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not misalign bolts - this will cause stripped threads, incorrect
                    mounting of cover, and leakage.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure bolts are aligned correctly with tapped holes in crankcase and in position for
                correct installation.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651129" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D13101.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Torquing bolts for high-pressure oil pump cover</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the other six M6 x 25 mounting bolts and tighten all eight bolts to the special
                torque .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new O-rings and backup ring on the IPR valve.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate O-ring with clean engine oil.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install IPR valve and tighten to the special torque .</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, disconnect the main battery negative terminal before
                    disconnecting or connecting electrical components.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2651103" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD09/D09122.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>IPR valve and engine harness connector</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">IPR valve</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Engine harness connector</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect engine harness connector to IPR valve.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Some engines have a metal heat shield mounted over the IPR valve; others have an insolated snap
                    shield on the IPR valve solenoid.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the correct heat shield for IPR valve:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>
                        <emph type="bold">Metal heat shield</emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                    <para>Install three mounting bolts in rear of exhaust heat shield and the two bolts in IPR valve
                        heat shield and tighten to the special torque
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>
                        <emph type="bold">Snap heat shield</emph>
                    </para>
                    <para>Install shield around the IPR valve cap and electrical connection and snap to connect.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reinstall all safety guards, shields, and covers.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure all tools, cleanliness covers, loose parts, and service equipment are removed from
                the engine work area.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
